article.headline: ETSU 78, Kennesaw St. 66
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Brad Nuckles scored 18 points, including 8 in overtime, and had a game-high 12 rebounds to lift East Tennessee State to a 78-66 victory Friday night over Kennesaw State. East Tennessee (14-7, 8-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) won its fifth straight game and snapped a three-game winning steak by the Owls (8-13, 4-5). The Owls made only 1-of-10 floor shots in overtime and were outscored 17-5. The final tie in overtime was at 65 on two free throws by the Owls' Golden Ingle, his only points of the game. ETSU had a 14-point margin at the free throw line, making 26-of-32 to Kennesaw's 12-of-23. Courtney Pigram added 15 points for ETSU, Eryk Thomas had 14 and Mike Smith 10. Ronell Wooten scored 26 for the Owls and had 10 rebounds while teammate Shuan Stegall scored 22. Jon-Michael Nickerson's layup for Kennesaw with 20 seconds left in regulation tied it 61-61. The Owls led 33-28 at the half after leading by seven points three times in the first half.
